    {
      "id": 93815424,
      "date": "2026-03-12",
      "name": "NP-W3 10-second Neuromuscular Power Bursts",
      "type": "WORKOUT",
      "planned_tss": 100,
      "duration_hours": 1.53,
      "duration_formatted": "1h31m40s",
      "workout_summary": "15m @186W | 20\u00d72m55s @222W / 10s rec | 15m @186W",
      "description": "NP-W3 Workout\n\n# Warm-up\n-15m 56-75% 69-83%HR\n\n# Tempo riding with bursts\n20x\n-2m55s 76-80% 84-88%HR\n-10s 180% 100+rpm\n\n# Cruise\n-Remaining time 56-75% 69-83%HR\n\n# Cooldown\n-15m 56-75% 69-83%HR\n\n---\nAnswer from Perplexity: pplx.ai/share\n\nAfter a standard warm-up, set a pace in the lower end of Level 3 (76\u201380 percent of FTP) and hold it steady for the next hour. Within this hour, do a 10-second, out-of-the-saddle burst every 3 minutes, trying to reach 180 percent of FTP wattage, and hold it there with no more than two gear changes, if any. Make sure your cadence stays high. Cruise the rest of the ride at below 80 percent of FTP.\n\nAllen, Hunter; Coggan, Andrew R.; McGregor, Stephen. Training and Racing with a Power Meter: Third Edition (p. 521). (Function). Kindle Edition."
    },
    {
      "id": 93815425,
      "date": "2026-03-13",
      "name": "LT-W10 Lactate Threshold with Anaerobic Capacity Intervals and Cadence Drills",
      "type": "WORKOUT",
      "planned_tss": 139,
      "duration_hours": 1.8,
      "duration_formatted": "1h48m",
      "workout_summary": "15m @186W | 3\u00d71m @289W / 1m rec | 4\u00d710m @289W / 5m rec | 4\u00d71m @399W / 2m rec | 15m @186W",
      "description": "LT-W10 Workout\n\n# Warm-up\n-15m 56-75% 69-83%HR\n\n# Fast pedaling\n3x\n-1m 100-103% 110+rpm\n-1m Z1\n\n# FTP intervals 5-10m Z1\n4x\n-10m 100-103% 100-105%HR\n-5m Z1\n\n# All-out efforts\n4x\n-1m >140% >105%HR\n-2m Z1\n\n# Cooldown\n-15m 56-75% 69-83%HR\n\nWarm up for 15 minutes in Level 2. Begin fast pedaling intervals with the goal of pedaling at 110+ rpm for the entire minute. Don\u2019t worry about power or heart rate. Recover for 1 minute between intervals. Then push hard and increase your cadence by 5 rpm for four 10-minute intervals at 100 percent of FTP. Rest for 5\u201310 minutes between efforts. Finish with four 1-minute intervals. Attack at the beginning of each interval, pushing as hard as you can. Rest for 2 minutes between efforts. Finish the ride with a 15-minute cooldown.\n\nAllen, Hunter; Coggan, Andrew R.; McGregor, Stephen. Training and Racing with a Power Meter: Third Edition (p. 502). (Function). Kindle Edition."
    },
